            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle, then heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a large heatproof bowl with your <strong>diced apricots</strong> and <strong>couscous</strong></p><p>Once the kettle has boiled, add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, stir, cover and set aside – this is your <strong>fruity couscous</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1626444877734-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1626444877734-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1626444877734-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1626444877734-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1626444877734-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, once the pan is hot, add your <strong>meat-free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, add your <strong>baharat</strong>, <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong> and <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
